    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-06-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-06-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="567"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d567">
                <head>[Memorandum.]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-06-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 26, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary of State presents his compliments to the French ambassador, and
                    with reference to the memorandum left at the Department of State by the chargé
                    d’affaires ad interim of France on December 26, 1899, expressing the wish of the
                    French Government that the claims of its citizens sufferers in Samoa should be
                    included in the arbitration provided for by the convention concluded November 7,
                    1899, between the Governments of the United States, Great Britain, and Germany,
                    has the honor to inclose for the information of the French ambassador a copy of
                    a memorandum<note n="1" xml:id="d567fn1">Printed <ref target="#pg_626">page
                            626</ref>.</note> addressed to the British ambassador on the 25th
                    instant, stating that this proposition is acceptable to the Government of the
                    United States provided it shall be agreeable to the Governments of Great Britain
                    and Germany.</p>
            </div>
